課程概述 Course Description
       This course prepares nurses and health related professions to teach in the schools, staff-development settings, and patient education programs. It is composed of theory in curriculum, instructional design, teaching strategies, instructional media, clinical teaching, and management that is applicable in classroom and clinical teaching. 

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    Course Objectives:
Upon completion of the course, the students will be able to:
Demonstrate self-directive, creative, and accountable attitude while pursuing their    individualized learning needs and interests relating to education in their fields.
Synthesize related concepts and theories appropriate to clinical instruction.
Analyze theories of measurement and evaluation as they relate to the various facets of education.
Design systems for innovative individual and group instruction in nursing or health related professions.
Synthesize course materials in curriculum building or clinical teaching.    

